LSE to Push Listings for Smaller U.S. Companies, Telegraph Says

-- B y   E m m a   C h a r l t o n
-- 
2011-06-05T08:17:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/lse-to-push-listings-for-smaller-u-s-companies-telegraph-says.html
The  London Stock Exchange Group Plc (LSE) 
plans to push its listing offering for smaller U.S. companies
once it completes its takeover of  TMX Group Inc. (X) , the  Sunday
Telegraph  reported, without saying where it got the information.  The company will use the deal to increase the market share
of its junior AIM market in the U.S., according to the
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Charlton in London at 
 echarlton1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net . 